<subSubSection lastPageId="83" lastPageNumber="84" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="82.[189,303,1884,1910]" box="[189,303,1884,1910]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1884,1910]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1884,1910]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="82.[189,1399,1930,2027]" lastBlockId="83.[189,1399,267,364]" lastPageId="83" lastPageNumber="84" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
The type male is unusually dull and matt yellow-orange, but it is also very dirty and the matt appearance may be the result of problems with moulds. The species is distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1258,1398,1966,1991]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1258,1398,1966,1991]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Mesoconius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without a strongly swollen katatergite by the absence of any distinguishing colour such as femoral bands, pigmented tarsi or notal pigmentation. The head chaetotaxy is damaged, but notes on the 
<typeStatus box="[1348,1399,268,294]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">type</typeStatus>
taken in 
<collectingRegion box="[296,369,302,328]" country="Germany" name="Berlin" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Berlin</collectingRegion>
in 2001 record the presence of outer vertical bristles, thus putting this species in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[189,287,339,364]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nono">
<emphasis box="[189,287,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">M. nono</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
